commands.help:
Usage: heroku commands [flags]

list all commands

Flags:
 --json

Usage: heroku help [SUBJECT] [flags]

display help

Aliases:
  $ heroku -h

Flags:
 --all  show all commands

Usage: heroku update [CHANNEL]

update the heroku CLI

Usage: heroku version

show CLI version

Aliases:
  $ heroku -v
  $ heroku --version

commands.description: show which plugin a command is from
commands.help:
Usage: heroku which COMMAND

show which plugin a command is from
helpLine: show which plugin a command is from

commands.help:
Usage: heroku plugins [flags]

list installed plugins

Flags:
 --core  show core plugins

Example:
    $ heroku plugins
    heroku-ci 1.8.0
    heroku-cli-status 3.0.10
    heroku-fork 4.1.22

commands.description: installs a plugin into the CLI
commands.help:
Usage: heroku plugins:install PLUGIN... [flags]

installs a plugin into the CLI

PLUGIN  plugin to install

Flags:
 -f, --force

Example:
    $ heroku plugins:install heroku-production-status
helpLine: installs a plugin into the CLI

commands.description: links a local plugin to the CLI for development
commands.help:
Usage: heroku plugins:link [PATH] [flags]

links a local plugin to the CLI for development

PATH  local file path to plugin root

Flags:
 -f, --force

Example:
    $ heroku plugins:link .
    Installing dependencies for /Users/dickeyxxx/src/github.com/heroku/heroku-status... done
    Running prepare script for /Users/dickeyxxx/src/github.com/heroku/heroku-status... done
helpLine: links a local plugin to the CLI for development

commands.help:
Usage: heroku plugins:uninstall PLUGIN

uninstalls or unlinks a plugin

Aliases:
  $ heroku plugins:unlink

PLUGIN  plugin name to uninstall

Example:
    $ heroku plugins:uninstall heroku-accounts

Usage: heroku plugins:update

update installed plugins
